n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Morocco}} \u2013 [[Party of Progress and Socialism]] abandoned [[Marxism\u2013Leninism]] for [[Democratic socialism]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Mozambique}} \u2013 [[Mozambique Liberation Front]] (FRELIMO), abandoned [[Marxism\u2013Leninism]] for [[social democracy]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Netherlands}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of the Netherlands]], merged with [[GroenLinks]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|North Macedonia}} \u2013 [[League of Communists of Macedonia]] abandoned [[Marxism\u2013Leninism]]\u2013[[Titoism]] for [[social democracy]], and became [[Social Democratic Union of Macedonia]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Poland}} \u2013 [[Polish United Workers' Party]], became [[Democratic Left Alliance]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Romania}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of Romania]], became [[National Salvation Front (Romania)|National Salvation Front]] the descendants of which are [[Democratic Liberal Party (Romania)|Democratic Liberal Party]] and [[Social Democratic Party (Romania)|Social Democratic Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|San Marino}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of San Marino]], became [[Party of Democrats]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Slovenia}} \u2013 [[League of Communists of Slovenia]] abandoned [[Marxism\u2013Leninism]]\u2013[[Titoism]] for [[social democracy]], and became [[Social Democrats (Slovenia)|Social Democrats]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Serbia}} \u2013 [[League of Communists of Serbia]] abandoned [[Marxism\u2013Leninism]]\u2013[[Titoism]] for [[democratic socialism]] and [[nationalism]], later [[social democracy]], and became [[Socialist Party of Serbia]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Tunisia}} \u2013 [[Tunisian Communist Party]], became [[Movement for Renewal]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Yemen}} \u2013 [[Yemeni Socialist Party]], abandoned [[Marxism\u2013Leninism]] for [[social democracy]]\n\n== Defunct ==\n=== Once ruling ===\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Afghanistan}} \u2013 [[People's Democratic Party of Afghanistan]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Albania}} \u2013 [[Party of Labour of Albania]] became [[Socialist Party of Albania]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Benin}} \u2013 [[People's Revolutionary Party of Benin]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Bulgaria}} \u2013 [[Bulgarian Communist Party]] became [[Bulgarian Socialist Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Cambodia}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of Kampuchea]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Czechoslovakia}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of Czechoslovakia]], Czech Republic branch became [[Communist Party of Bohemia and Moravia]] and Slovak branch became the [[Party of the Democratic Left (Slovakia)|Party of the Democratic Left]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Ethiopia}} \u2013 [[Workers' Party of Ethiopia]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Germany}} \u2013 [[Party of Democratic Socialism (Germany)|Party of Democratic Socialism]] (now a part of [[The Left (Germany)|The Left]])\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Grenada}} \u2013 [[New Jewel Movement]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Hungary}} \u2013 [[Hungarian Working People's Party]], [[Hungarian Socialist Workers' Party]] became [[Hungarian Socialist Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Poland}} \u2013 [[Polish United Workers' Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Romania}} \u2013 [[Romanian Communist Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Somalia}} \u2013 [[Somali Revolutionary Socialist Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Soviet Union}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of the Soviet Union]], previously the [[Bolshevik]] faction of the [[Russian Social Democratic Labour Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|