ty of Canada]] was banned (resumed former name in 1959), [[Workers' Communist Party of Canada]]\n* [[List of political parties in the Channel Islands|Channel Islands]] \u2013 [[Jersey Communist Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Taiwan}} \u2013 [[Taiwanese Communist Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Chile}} \u2013 [[Chilean Communist Party (Proletarian Action)]], [[Revolutionary Left Movement (Chile)|Revolutionary Left Movement]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Colombia}} \u2013 [[Workers Revolutionary Party of Colombia]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Costa Rica}} \u2013 [[Costa Rican People's Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Cyprus}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of Cyprus]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Cuba}} \u2013 [[Popular Socialist Party (Cuba)|Popular Socialist Party]], joined [[Cuban Communist Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|El Salvador}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of El Salvador]], merged into the [[FMLN]]\n* [[List of political parties in the Free Territory of Trieste|Free Territory of Trieste]] \u2013 [[Communist Party of the Free Territory of Trieste]], merged into the [[Italian Communist Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Georgia}} \u2013 [[Revived Communist Party of Georgia]], [[Georgian Workers Communist Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Germany}} \u2013 [[Spartacist League]] formed in 1918 and became the [[Communist Party of Germany]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|West Germany}} \u2013 [[Socialist Unity Party of West Berlin]], [[Communist Party of Germany]] (banned 1956 in West Germany)\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Guatemala}} \u2013 [[Guatemalan Party of Labour]], merged into the [[URNG]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Haiti}} \u2013 [[Haitian Workers Party]], [[Unified Party of Haitian Communists]], merged into the [[National Reconstruction Movement]] in 1990\n* {{fl