ies in|India}} \u2013 [[Indian Communist Party (Sen)]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Indonesia}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of Indonesia]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Ireland}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of Ireland (Marxist\u2013Leninist)]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Iraq}} \u2013 [[Leninist Group in the Iraqi Communist Movement]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Israel}} \u2013 [[Maki (historical political party)|Maki]] (1948\u20131973) split in 1965 with formation of largely Arab [[Maki (current political party)|Rakah]] which changed its name to Maki in 1989\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Italy}} \u2013 [[Italian Communist Party of the Julian March]], [[Communist Party of Italy]], [[Marxist\u2013Leninist Revolutionary Party of Italy]], [[Movement for Peace and Socialism]], [[Movement for the Confederation of the Communists]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Lebanon}} \u2013 [[Lebanese People's Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Malaysia}} \u2013 [[Malayan Communist Party]], [[North Kalimantan Communist Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Mexico}} \u2013 [[Mexican Communist Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Moldova}} \u2013 [[Communist Reformers Party of Moldova]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Namibia}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of Namibia (1981)|Communist Party of Namibia]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Netherlands}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of the Netherlands]] merged into [[GroenLinks]] in 1989\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|New Zealand}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of New Zealand]], [[Socialist Unity Party of New Zealand|Socialist Unity Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Nigeria}} \u2013 [[Nigerian Communist Party]], [[Socialist Workers and Farmers Party of Nigeria]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Norway}} \u2013 [[Workers' Communist Party (Norway)|Workers' Communist Party]] merged into the [[Red Party (Norway)|Red Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Palestine}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of Palestine]] (1921\u20131948)\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Poland}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of Poland]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Saudi Arabia}} \u2013 [[Communist Party in Saudi Arabia]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Swaziland}} \u2013 [[Swaziland Communist Party]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Switzerland}} \u2013 [[Party of Labour Basel]] (founded in 1944)\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Tatarstan}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of the Republic of Tatarstan]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Thailand}} \u2013 [[Communist Party of Thailand]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|United States}} \u2013 [[Communist Party (Marxist\u2013Leninist) (United States)|Communist Party Marxist\u2013Leninist]], [[May 19th Communist Movement]], [[Communist Workers' Party (United States)|Communist Workers Party]], [[Black Panther Party]], [[Communist Labor Party of America]], [[International Socialist Organization]]\n\n== Left communist organizations by country ==\nThe following is alist of left communist organizations by country which list only those political organizations and parties who officially call themselves [[Left communism|left communist]] ideologically and still exist.\n\n=== Organisations ===\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Italy}} \u2013 [[Internationalist Communist Party (Battaglia Comunista)|Internationalist Communist Party (Communist Battle)]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Italy}} \u2013 [[Lotta Comunista]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|United Kingdom}} \u2013 [[Communist Workers Organisation (UK)|Communist Workers Organisation]], [[World Revolution (UK)|World Revolution]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|United States}} \u2013 Internationalism, [[Internationalist Workers Group (US)|Internationalist Workers Group]], [[Workers Offensive (US)|Workers Offensive]]\n* {{flag+link|List of political parties in|Venezuela}} \u2013 [[Internationalism (Venezuela)|Internationalism]]\n\n== See also ==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Communist party]]\n* [[Communist Party (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Communist state]]\n* [[History of communism]]\n* [[History of socialism]]\n* [[International Communist Seminar]]\n* [[International Coordination of Revolutionary Parties and Organizations]]\n* [[International Meeting of Communist and Workers' Parties]]\n* [[List of active communist armed groups]]\n* [[List of anarchist organizations]]\n* [[List of anti-capitalist and communist parties with national parliamentary representation]]\n* [[List of communist parties represented in European Parliament]]\n* [[List of left-wing internationals]]\n* [[List of socialist states]]\n* [[List of Trotskyist internationals]]\n* [[List of Trotskyist organizations by country]]\n* [[Socialist state]]\n}}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External link s==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100209092451/http://www.broadleft.org/index.htm Leftist Parties of the World] (last updated 4 October 2006)\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8tOL-f_KsaA Communist States animation (1850-2016)]\n\n{{world topic|List of communist parties in|title=Lists of communist parties by country|noredlinks=yes}}\n[[Category:Communist parties by country|*]]\n[[Category:Lists of political parties|Communist]]\n", "name_user": "Davide King", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eOne-party system:ce", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_communist_parties"}
